column1:
Asics Europe, a shoes and clothing retailer, ran an online referral campaign during April of 2018. In that month, existing users provided a referral code to new users. When a new user made a first purchase using a referral code, the referrer received a €10 (10 Euros) credit toward a future order. This Milestone uses data from this marketing campaign.

The data is provided in two tables, each on their own page of the workbook. The Orders worksheet contains information about randomly sampled orders made during the recording period. The Users worksheet contains information about the users that made purchases during the recording period.

For this task, you'll engage the following skills:

(1) Prepare the data by transforming it.
(2) Calculate spending among referral and non-referral customers. 
(3) Summarize the orders and user data by creating PivotTables.
